having already made use of the albion woods facility, [shelter house, men's and ladies' bathrooms, wet bar, swings for the kiddies, cookstoves, etc.] albeit some 17 years ago, there was no ranger presence required, nor do i remember any of them having ever visited, throughout the course of the entire day.

 

of course, this was "back in the day" so to speak, and i don't know if their policy has changed, or not.  as i recall, i seem to remember some regulation about there being canned beer only, but we had a keg, and not one problem with it.

 

well...  aside from the massive inebriation, of course.  :)
